---
import QuestionLayout from '@layouts/QuestionLayout.astro';

const relatedLinks = [];
const _body = "<p>Traverse turns a request into a result through a deterministic, multi-step execution pipeline. Every step is logged. Every failure is recorded. The same binary with the same inputs always produces the same output.</p>\n\n      <h2>The execution steps</h2>\n      <ol class=\"step-list\">\n        <li><strong>Request arrives</strong> with a goal and a requested placement target (e.g. <span class=\"code-inline\">local</span>).</li>\n        <li><strong>Registry discovery</strong> searches all loaded capabilities for ones that declare the requested goal and support the placement target.</li>\n        <li><strong>Constraint evaluation</strong> checks preconditions on each candidate. Capabilities that fail preconditions are removed from the selection pool.</li>\n        <li><strong>Selection</strong> picks the best remaining capability. If none qualify, the machine moves to <span class=\"code-inline\">error</span> with <span class=\"code-inline\">capability_not_found</span>.</li>\n        <li><strong>WASM binary loads</strong> into an isolated sandbox. Sandbox permissions are taken from the contract. By default, <span class=\"code-inline\">network_access</span>, <span class=\"code-inline\">filesystem_access</span>, and <span class=\"code-inline\">host_api_access</span> are all false.</li>\n        <li><strong>Input validation</strong> checks the caller's inputs against the contract's input schema. Invalid inputs stop execution before the binary runs.</li>\n        <li><strong>Entrypoint is called</strong> with the validated inputs.</li>\n        <li><strong>Output validation</strong> checks the returned value against the contract's output schema. A mismatch triggers <span class=\"code-inline\">postcondition_failed</span>.</li>\n        <li><strong>Events are emitted.</strong> The runtime enters the <span class=\"code-inline\">emitting_events</span> state and publishes all output events declared in the contract.</li>\n        <li><strong>Trace artifact is produced.</strong> A structured JSON record captures every step, decision, and timing for this execution.</li>\n      </ol>\n\n      <h2>Sandbox defaults</h2>\n      <p>Unless a capability's contract explicitly enables a permission, the WASM instance cannot reach outside the sandbox. These three flags cover the main host capabilities:</p>\n      <div class=\"code-block\">network_access:     false  # no outbound HTTP\nfilesystem_access:  false  # no file I/O\nhost_api_access:    false  # no OS calls</div>\n      <p>A capability that tries to use a host API it did not declare will fail at the WASM level. The contract is the spec and the enforcer.</p>\n\n      <h2>Determinism</h2>\n      <p>WASM execution is deterministic by design. The same binary with the same validated inputs produces the same output every time. This matters for testing, auditing, and reproducing failures from a trace artifact.</p>\n\n      <h2>What the state machine looks like</h2>\n      <div class=\"code-block\">idle\n  → loading_registry\n  → ready\n  → discovering\n  → evaluating_constraints\n  → selecting\n  → executing\n  → emitting_events\n  → completed | error</div>\n      <p>Each arrow is a logged transition. If the machine stops at <span class=\"code-inline\">error</span>, the trace tells you exactly which state failed and why.</p>";
const _jsonLd = "{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How does Traverse execute WASM?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Traverse matches a request to a capability, validates constraints and preconditions, loads the WASM binary into an isolated sandbox, validates inputs, calls the entrypoint, validates outputs, emits events, and produces a trace artifact.\"}}]}";
---
<QuestionLayout
  title={"How does Traverse execute WASM?"}
  description={"Step-by-step: how Traverse takes a request, discovers a matching capability, validates constraints, loads the WASM binary, validates I/O, and produces a trace artifact."}
  canonical={"https://traverse-framework.com/questions/how-does-traverse-execute-wasm.html"}
  category={"Technical Architecture"}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  jsonLd={_jsonLd}
>
  <Fragment set:html={_body} />
</QuestionLayout>
